        keyFormula: "Net Assets = Assets - Liabilities (With Donor Restrictions + Without Donor Restrictions)",
        lesson: "<p>NFP entities classify net assets into two categories: with donor restrictions (purpose or time restrictions) and without donor restrictions. When restrictions are satisfied, a reclassification is reported: decrease in \u2018with\u2019 and increase in \u2018without.\u2019 Contributions are recognized at fair value when received if unconditional.</p><p>Conditional promises to give (those with barriers and a right of return/release) are not recognized until conditions are substantially met. Contributed services are recognized only when they (1) create or enhance a nonfinancial asset, or (2) require specialized skills, are provided by persons with those skills, and would typically be purchased if not donated.</p><p>Required statements: Statement of Financial Position, Statement of Activities (showing changes in each net asset class), Statement of Cash Flows, and Statement of Functional Expenses (or note disclosure). Expenses must be reported by function (program services, management and general, fundraising) and by nature.</p>",
