        keyFormula: "Basic EPS = (Net Income - Preferred Dividends) / Weighted-Average Common Shares Outstanding",
        lesson: "<p>Public companies file Form 10-K (annual, audited, within 60 days for large accelerated filers), 10-Q (quarterly, reviewed, within 40 days), and 8-K (current events, within 4 business days for most items). The 10-K includes audited financial statements, MD&A, selected financial data, and ICFR assessment.</p><p>Basic EPS uses net income minus preferred dividends in the numerator and weighted-average common shares in the denominator. Stock splits and stock dividends are retroactively adjusted as if they occurred at the beginning of the earliest period presented. For cumulative preferred, the annual dividend amount is deducted whether or not declared.</p><p>Diluted EPS assumes exercise of dilutive securities. Treasury stock method for options/warrants: assume exercised at beginning of period, proceeds used to buy back shares at average market price, net new shares added to denominator. If-converted method for convertible bonds: add back after-tax interest to numerator and conversion shares to denominator. For convertible preferred: add back preferred dividends and add conversion shares. Antidilutive securities (those that increase EPS) are excluded.</p>",
