        lesson: "<p>Cash includes currency, checking accounts, and items acceptable for deposit. Cash equivalents have original maturities of three months or less (Treasury bills, money market funds, commercial paper). Restricted cash must be separately disclosed.</p><p>Under ASC 326 (CECL model), entities measure expected credit losses over the lifetime of financial assets measured at amortized cost. This forward-looking model replaces the incurred loss model. The allowance reflects management\u2019s estimate of all expected losses, considering historical data, current conditions, and reasonable and supportable forecasts.</p><p>The allowance method requires estimating uncollectible accounts at each reporting date. The aging method categorizes receivables by days past due and applies increasing loss percentages. Write-offs reduce both the receivable and allowance with no impact on net realizable value or bad debt expense. Recoveries reverse the write-off entry first, then record the cash collection.</p>",
