        objectives: ["Account for bonds at par, premium, and discount using the effective interest method","Record bond retirement, defeasance, and conversion","Account for notes payable and debt covenants"],
        keyFormula: "Bond Price = PV of Interest Annuity + PV of Face Value (at market rate). Interest Expense = Carrying Amount x Market Rate.",
        lesson: "<p>Bonds are issued at par when stated rate equals market rate, at a premium when stated rate exceeds market rate, and at a discount when stated rate is below market rate. Under ASC 835, bond issue costs are netted against the carrying amount (presented as a deduction from the liability).</p><p>Under the effective interest method, interest expense equals the carrying amount times the market rate at issuance. Cash payment equals face value times stated rate. The difference amortizes the premium or discount. Premium amortization decreases carrying amount toward face value; discount amortization increases it.</p><p>Early retirement: compare the reacquisition price (call price or market price) to the net carrying amount. The difference is a gain or loss in net income. Convertible bonds converted to stock under the book value method transfer the entire carrying amount to equity with no gain or loss. Induced conversion costs are expensed. Debt covenants must be monitored; violation may require reclassification to current.</p>",
