        keyFormula: "5 Steps: 1) Identify contract 2) Identify obligations 3) Determine price 4) Allocate price 5) Recognize when satisfied",
        lesson: "<p>ASC 606 establishes a comprehensive framework. Step 1: Identify the contract (approval, rights, payment terms, commercial substance, collectibility). Step 2: Identify distinct performance obligations (capable of being distinct + separately identifiable). Step 3: Determine the transaction price including variable consideration (estimated using expected value or most likely amount), constrained to amounts not expected to significantly reverse.</p><p>Step 4: Allocate transaction price to performance obligations based on relative standalone selling prices. Methods to estimate SSP: adjusted market assessment, expected cost plus margin, residual approach (limited use). Step 5: Recognize revenue when (or as) each obligation is satisfied by transferring control.</p><p>Over-time recognition applies when: customer simultaneously receives and consumes benefits, entity creates customer-controlled asset, or asset has no alternative use plus right to payment for performance to date. Point-in-time indicators: right to payment, legal title, physical possession, risks and rewards transferred, customer acceptance. Contract costs: costs to obtain (capitalize if incremental, amortize) and costs to fulfill (capitalize if directly related, generate resources, expected to be recovered).</p>",
