        lesson: "<p>A security interest under UCC Article 9 gives a creditor rights in collateral. Attachment requires three elements: the creditor gives value, the debtor has rights in the collateral, and there is a security agreement (authenticated writing or possession). Perfection establishes priority against third parties through filing a financing statement, taking possession, or control (deposit accounts).</p><p>Priority among secured creditors: perfected secured creditors have priority over unperfected. Among perfected creditors, first to file or perfect wins. Purchase money security interests (PMSI) have super-priority if perfected within 20 days (goods other than inventory) or before debtor receives possession (inventory with notice to other secured parties).</p><p>Bankruptcy: Chapter 7 (liquidation) appoints a trustee to liquidate non-exempt assets. Chapter 11 (reorganization) allows the business to continue while restructuring debt. Chapter 13 (individual repayment plan) for individuals with regular income. Priority of claims: secured creditors, then administrative expenses, then priority unsecured (wages up to $15,150, employee benefits, taxes), then general unsecured.</p>",
