        lesson: "<p>MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) is the tax depreciation system. Key recovery periods: 3 years (tractor units), 5 years (autos, computers, office equipment), 7 years (office furniture, fixtures), 15 years (land improvements, qualified improvement property), 27.5 years (residential rental, straight-line), 39 years (nonresidential real property, straight-line).</p><p>Conventions: half-year (most property), mid-quarter (if >40% placed in service in Q4), and mid-month (real property). The half-year convention allows a half-year of depreciation in the first and last year. Personal property generally uses 200% DB switching to SL; 15-year uses 150% DB.</p><p>Section 179 allows immediate expensing of qualifying property up to the annual dollar limit (adjusted annually for inflation, approximately $1.29 million for 2026). The deduction cannot exceed taxable income from active business. Bonus depreciation under the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act was 100% through 2022, reduced to 80% (2023), 60% (2024), 40% (2025), and 20% (2026). Note: H.R. 1 (One Big Beautiful Bill Act) provisions may extend or modify bonus depreciation rates; check effective dates for the July 2026 exam window.</p>",
