        lesson: "<p>Filing statuses: Single, Married Filing Jointly, Married Filing Separately, Head of Household (unmarried + maintained home for qualifying person for >50% of year + paid >50% of household costs), Qualifying Surviving Spouse (2 years after spouse\u2019s death, with dependent child). MFJ generally produces the lowest tax.</p><p>Dependents: qualifying child (relationship, age under 19 or 24 if student, residency >50% of year, not self-supporting >50%) or qualifying relative (relationship or member of household, gross income < exemption amount, support >50% provided by taxpayer). Multiple support agreements apply when no single person provides >50% support.</p><p>Key credits: Child Tax Credit (CTC) up to $2,000 per qualifying child under 17 with refundable portion (H.R. 1 may modify the amounts and age thresholds). Earned Income Tax Credit (EITC) is fully refundable and varies by number of children and income. Child and Dependent Care Credit (nonrefundable, 20-35% of up to $3,000/$6,000 expenses). American Opportunity Credit ($2,500, 40% refundable). Lifetime Learning Credit ($2,000, nonrefundable). Estimated tax: pay 100% of prior year tax or 90% of current year tax (110% of prior year if AGI >$150,000) to avoid underpayment penalty.</p>",
