        lesson: "<p>Section 501(c)(3) organizations must be organized and operated exclusively for religious, charitable, scientific, literary, or educational purposes. They must not engage in substantial lobbying or any political campaign activity. Private foundations face additional restrictions: excise tax on net investment income, required minimum distributions, prohibition on self-dealing, limits on excess business holdings.</p><p>Unrelated business taxable income (UBTI) applies to income from a trade or business regularly carried on that is not substantially related to the exempt purpose. Key exclusions from UBTI: investment income (dividends, interest, rents, royalties), gains from sale of property, volunteer labor activities, convenience activities, and activities where substantially all work is performed by volunteers. UBTI is subject to regular corporate or trust tax rates.</p><p>LLCs are classified for tax purposes under the check-the-box rules. A single-member LLC is a disregarded entity (Schedule C for individuals, Schedule F for farms). A multi-member LLC defaults to partnership taxation. LLCs may elect to be taxed as a C or S corporation. The entity classification affects all aspects of taxation including self-employment tax, employment tax, and information reporting.</p>",
