        keyFormula: "DuPont: ROE = Profit Margin x Asset Turnover x Equity Multiplier = (NI/Sales) x (Sales/Assets) x (Assets/Equity)",
        lesson: "<p>Liquidity ratios: current ratio (CA/CL), quick ratio ((Cash + ST Investments + Net Receivables)/CL), cash ratio (Cash/CL). Profitability: gross margin (GP/Sales), operating margin (OI/Sales), net profit margin (NI/Sales), ROA (NI/Avg Total Assets), ROE (NI/Avg Equity). Activity: inventory turnover (COGS/Avg Inventory), receivables turnover (Net Credit Sales/Avg AR), asset turnover (Sales/Avg Total Assets).</p><p>Solvency ratios: debt-to-equity (Total Debt/Total Equity), debt-to-assets (Total Debt/Total Assets), times interest earned (EBIT/Interest Expense), cash coverage (EBITDA/Interest). The cash conversion cycle = days inventory outstanding + days sales outstanding - days payable outstanding.</p><p>DuPont analysis decomposes ROE into three drivers: profitability (net margin), efficiency (asset turnover), and leverage (equity multiplier). Horizontal analysis compares amounts across periods (trend analysis). Vertical analysis expresses each line item as a percentage of a base (typically total assets for BS, net sales for IS). Common-size statements facilitate comparisons across entities of different sizes.</p>",
