        keyFormula: "Price Variance = (AP - SP) x AQ. Quantity Variance = (AQ - SQ) x SP. Total Variance = Actual - Standard.",
        lesson: "<p>Direct materials variances: Materials Price Variance = (Actual Price - Standard Price) x Actual Quantity purchased. Materials Quantity (Usage) Variance = (Actual Quantity used - Standard Quantity allowed) x Standard Price. Price variance is often the responsibility of purchasing; quantity variance is the responsibility of production.</p><p>Direct labor variances: Labor Rate Variance = (Actual Rate - Standard Rate) x Actual Hours. Labor Efficiency Variance = (Actual Hours - Standard Hours allowed) x Standard Rate. Rate variance responsibility: HR/management. Efficiency variance responsibility: production supervisors.</p><p>Variable overhead: Spending Variance = Actual VOH - (Actual Hours x Standard VOH Rate). Efficiency Variance = (Actual Hours - Standard Hours) x Standard VOH Rate. Fixed overhead: Budget Variance = Actual FOH - Budgeted FOH. Volume Variance = Budgeted FOH - Applied FOH = (Normal Capacity Hours - Standard Hours Allowed) x Standard FOH Rate. Volume variance measures capacity utilization, not spending efficiency.</p>",
