        lesson: "<p>Variable costs change in total proportionally with activity but remain constant per unit. Fixed costs remain constant in total within the relevant range but decrease per unit as activity increases. Mixed costs have both fixed and variable components (separated using high-low method, scatterplot, or regression).</p><p>CVP analysis assumes linear cost behavior within the relevant range. Contribution margin = Sales - Variable Costs. CM ratio = CM / Sales. Breakeven point in units = Total Fixed Costs / CM per unit. Breakeven in dollars = Total Fixed Costs / CM ratio. For target profit: add target profit (pre-tax) to fixed costs in the numerator. For after-tax target: divide target by (1 - tax rate) first.</p><p>Operating leverage = CM / Operating Income. Higher operating leverage means greater sensitivity of profit to sales changes. Margin of safety = actual sales - breakeven sales. Multi-product CVP uses weighted-average CM based on the sales mix. Changes in sales mix affect the breakeven point even if total volume stays constant.</p>",
