        lesson: "<p>Under ASC 805, all business combinations use the acquisition method. The acquirer recognizes identifiable assets acquired and liabilities assumed at their acquisition-date fair values. Goodwill is measured as the excess of the aggregate of: consideration transferred, NCI fair value, and any previously held equity interest fair value, over the net identifiable assets.</p><p>Acquisition-related costs (due diligence, legal, advisory fees) are expensed as incurred. Stock issuance costs reduce APIC. Contingent consideration is measured at fair value at the acquisition date. Subsequent changes in contingent consideration classified as a liability go through income; equity-classified remains in equity.</p><p>A bargain purchase (negative goodwill) occurs when net identifiable assets exceed the total consideration. The acquirer must first reassess all measurements, then recognize any remaining excess as a gain in net income. The measurement period (up to one year) allows adjustments to provisional amounts as new information is obtained about facts existing at the acquisition date.</p>",
        practiceTip: "Acquisition costs are EXPENSED (except stock issuance costs to APIC). Bargain purchase = gain in income after reassessing all measurements."
