        objectives: ["Apply ASC 280 segment reporting requirements","Calculate basic and diluted EPS including complex capital structures","Account for research and development costs"],
        keyFormula: "Operating segment tests: 10% of revenue, profit/loss, or assets. 75% of external revenue must be reportable.",
        lesson: "<p>ASC 280 requires disclosure of operating segments that meet any of three quantitative thresholds: 10% of combined revenue, 10% of the greater of combined profit or combined loss, or 10% of combined assets. Reportable segments must represent at least 75% of total external revenue. If not, additional segments are added until the threshold is met.</p><p>Required segment disclosures include: revenue (external and intersegment), profit or loss measure, total assets, depreciation, capital expenditures, and certain other items. The management approach defines segments based on how the chief operating decision maker (CODM) evaluates performance and allocates resources.</p><p>Research and development costs (ASC 730) are expensed as incurred under U.S. GAAP. This includes salaries of R&D personnel, materials consumed, depreciation of R&D equipment (with no alternative future use), contract research, and indirect costs. Exception: software development costs are capitalized after technological feasibility is established (ASC 985-20) or after preliminary project stage for internal-use software (ASC 350-40).</p>",
        practiceTip: "R&D = expensed under GAAP. Software: capitalize after technological feasibility (external) or after preliminary stage (internal). Segments: 10% tests."
